NOTE: This strategy best works on SPY (S&P 500), on the Daily Timeframe. This is a strategy that has worked since 1960 and has returned a CAGR of 20%+. Over the past 30 years it has returned 25% CAGR, so pretty high. Although the one downside about this strategy is the max drawdown which is at 65% over the past 30 years so if you prefer a lower max drawdown then definitely lower the leverage down from 5x to 2-3x, please note your CAGR will also drop once you lower the leverage.
